The freak weather saw golf-ball-sized hail smashing through roofs, car windows and infrastructure in the area. Twitter/@tWeatherSA JOHANNESBURG - A hailstorm has left many Seshego residents in Polokwane homeless. The local municipality has availed the town hall to provide temporary shelter to displaced families. READ: Hout Bay fire leaves hundreds of people homeless The freak weather saw golf-ball-sized hail smashing through roofs, car windows and infrastructure in the area. A disaster management team will assess the damage on Thursday. Electricity has been switched on in most areas except for Luthuli Park, where roofs are still hanging from electrical lines.